                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.512/877: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-11-15T13:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 15, 1928—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>384. Your 828, November 13, 8 p.m. and preceding. Department heartily approves
                    note. In addition, you may inform Consuls General at Shanghai and Canton that
                    they may say that the Department is watching this and other cases closely and is
                    unfavorably impressed by accumulative evidence that various Chinese authorities
                    are indifferent not only to treaty rights but to processes and requirements of
                    municipal and international law.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
